{% block content %}
  <h2>Wildfire and evacuation</h2>
  <p>First Nations wildfire response in Ontario now runs on an Indigenous-led evacuation model, with communities leading the call and the province and Canada supporting. Know your community's emergency plan and where to register if an evacuation is called. Indigenous Services Canada funds wildfire prevention and emergency management for First Nations.</p>

  <h2>Winter and highway safety</h2>
  <p>Distances are long and help can be far on northern highways. Keep your gas tank above half. Carry a winter vehicle kit: a flashlight, reflective triangles or flares and a vest, a small shovel, a scraper, sand or grit for traction, a first-aid kit, food and water, and warm layers and blankets for everyone. Tell someone your route and arrival time before remote travel. If you are stranded, stay with the vehicle.</p>

  <h2>Outages and a household kit</h2>
  <p>Build a 72-hour household kit: water, non-perishable food, medications, a hand-crank or battery radio and flashlight, batteries, warmth, and copies of important documents. Check on Elders and neighbours during outages and cold snaps.</p>

